00:39:11,519 --> 00:39:13,700
So I had this shop in my basement when I was growing up.

659
00:39:15,861 --> 00:39:17,162
As soon as they thought I was old enough,

660
00:39:17,482 --> 00:39:19,843
my parents taught me how to use all the tools safely,

661
00:39:19,903 --> 00:39:22,164
what precautions to take, how they worked, what they did.

662
00:39:24,125 --> 00:39:25,626
My mother's work was folk art,

663
00:39:25,666 --> 00:39:27,487
which was a business that left her plenty of free time

664
00:39:27,527 --> 00:39:29,148
to spend with us kids for a good part of the year.

665
00:39:29,605 --> 00:39:31,486
The price was that in the months approaching Christmas,

666
00:39:31,526 --> 00:39:33,067
she was basically living down there

667
00:39:33,087 --> 00:39:34,288
and working every waking moment.

668
00:39:35,128 --> 00:39:37,750
During those busy times, she'd pay us to help.

669
00:39:39,031 --> 00:39:40,351
Most of her work was with standard

670
00:39:40,371 --> 00:39:41,732
three-quarter inch thick pine stock

